BundleParc-flow

USAGE

nextflow run scil-vital/BundleParc-flow -profile docker [OPTIONAL ARGUMENTS] (--dwi, --fodf)

DESCRIPTION

You can provide either diffusion weighted imaging (DWI) volumes input, incl. related bvecs and bvals, or fiber orientation distribution (FOD) volumes.

It is **strongly** recommended to use the --dwi input providing the files listed below. If you are completely sure your fODFs are in the correct format, you can skip fODF modelling by using the --fodf input: fODF **MUST** be in spherical harmonics (SH), `descoteaux07_legacy` basis of order 6 or 8, with stride of -1,2,3,4. If you have any doubts, it is recommended that you use the --dwi input instead.

You can provide DWI volumes:
    --dwi=/path/to/[input]   Input directory containing your subjects
                    |
                    ├-- S1
                    |    ├-- *dwi.nii.gz
                    |    ├-- *dwi.bval
                    |    ├-- *dwi.bvec"
                    |    └-- *rev_b0.nii.gz (optional)"
                    └-- S2
                         ├-- *dwi.nii.gz
                         ├-- *dwi.bval
                         ├-- *dwi.bvec"
                         └-- *rev_b0.nii.gz (optional)"


Or you can use fODF as input directly:
    --fodf=/path/to/[input]   Input directory containing your subjects
                    |
                    ├-- S1
                    |    ├-- *fodf.nii.gz
                    └-- S2
                         └-- *fodf.nii.gz

OPTIONAL ARGUMENTS:

    --preproc: Run preprocessing steps on the input DWI volumes -- denoising, gibbs, bet, topup, eddy, cropping, N4, normalization, resampling. Not necessary if your data is already preprocessed, ie coming from Tractoflow or if processing HCP data.
    --output: Output folder [default: 'result'].
    --eddy_max_concurrent: Nb. of proceses to run eddy. [default: 16].
    --vram: Size of your GPU, in GB. Will impact the number of BundleParc instances run in parallel [default: 24].
    --half_precision: Use half-precision floating points (float16) to reduce the VRAM needed to run BundleParc. May impact accuracy [default: false].
    --nb_pts: Nb. of bundle subdivisions [default: 10].
    --min_blob_size: Minimum size of 'blob' in output bundle to keep, in voxels [default: 50].
    --continuous: Output 'continuous' label maps ]0, 1] instead of discrete maps [default: false].
    --keep_biggest_blob: Only keep the biggest blob instead of removing smaller ones (< 50 voxels) [default: false]. 
    --mm: Produce label maps where each label has a specific 'thickness' (in mm.) instead of a fixed number of labels. Experimental, YMMV, but may be useful for smaller bundles [default: false].
